Sainsbury Says It Closed 16 Stores Because of Rioting in U.K.

-- B y   S a r a h   S h a n n o n
-- 
2011-08-09T11:47:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/sainsbury-says-it-closed-16-stores-because-of-rioting-in-u-k-.html
J Sainsbury Plc (SBRY) , the U.K.’s third-
largest supermarket chain, said 16 of its stores were forced to
close after "serious" incidents during last night’s riots.  Three convenience stores are still closed and the retailer
is assessing the situation on an hour-by-hour basis, the London-
based company said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Shannon in  London  at 
 sshannon4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 